BBC World News Focus On Africa producer and presenter Sophie Ikenye is mourning the death of her father Stephen Uno, who hails from Matathia area."My dad Stephen Uno rests in peace now. He has fulfilled the purpose for which he was created. He taught us many things, one of which is to be strong and the other to be honest in this life. Till we meet again. RIP," Sophie posted on social media.Her fans across the globe, including journalists, sent their condolences to the bereaved family."My condolences Sophie. Though Mzee is gone he leaves behind a great legacy no doubt. Mission accomplished. May his soul be at peace in heaven," Masibo said.Uno was the father to Sophie Ikenye, Ikenye Kemu, Njeri Ikenye and Ngugi Ikenye.